, Ellery Channing, and Charles Newcomb.   Author David Dowling's history of the professional and personal relationships between Emerson and his protégés-a remarkable collaboration that alternately proved fruitful and destructive, tension-filled and liberating-is a fascinating true story of altruism, ego, influence, pettiness, genius, and the bold attempt to reshape the literary market of the mid-nineteenth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2015z978311067250308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2016z978311053800708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300206760423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300206760.jpg  a978-3-11-053800-7  YUP eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-067250-3  YUP eBook Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles